## Lucide Icon Rule (mandatory)

When adding or editing `<lucide-icon name="...">` in any component template, you MUST also register the icon in `src/app/app.config.ts`.

**Two places to update — always both:**

1. **Import** the icon from `lucide-angular` (PascalCase):
   ```typescript
   import { CircleUserRound, ChefHat, Trash2 } from 'lucide-angular';
   ```

2. **Add** to `LucideAngularModule.pick({ ... })` in `app.config.ts`:
   ```typescript
   LucideAngularModule.pick({ CircleUserRound, ChefHat, Trash2 })
   ```

**Naming convention:**
- Template: kebab-case → `<lucide-icon name="circle-user-round">`
- TypeScript: PascalCase → `CircleUserRound`

**Missing registration causes this runtime error:**
> "The 'circle-user-round' icon has not been provided by any available icon providers."

This error only appears at runtime, not at build time — always register before committing.
